      <body>
         <entry xml:id="egdikos-ys"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#egdiqos-dlgenr"
            next="#agusta-ys"
            source="Yalkut Shimoni">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אגדיקוס</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾgdyqws</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic">egdiqos</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="corrupted">
                  <orth type="corrupted" xml:lang="jpa">אגריקוס</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb">ʾgryqws</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic">egriqos</pron>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="egdikos-ys-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>governor, prefect, public prosecutor</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>ἔκδικος</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>אין כל מקום ומקום שאין ממונה על בייא שלו, אנגיטוס [אגדיקוס*] במדינה ממונה על בייא שלו, 
                     <app>
                        <lem>אגריקוס</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W">אגריסוק [אגדיקוס*]</rdg>
                     </app> במדינה ממונה על בייא שלו כך מי ממונה על עולמו של הקדוש ברוך הוא הקדוש ברוך הוא ביה שמו, הקדוש ברוך הוא בייא של עולמו</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq Ps 794</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">463d: 20.21</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>There is not a single place which does not have an appointed [authority] over its dominion. The ‘egdikos’ in his province is appointed over its dominion; the ‘egdikos’ in his province is appointed over its dominion. Thus, who is appointed over the dominion of his world? The Holy One, blessed be He, be-yah is his name, biyyah is his name.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 10,12 (I 108:4)</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">yHag 2,1 (77c [786: 22])</bibl> (-); <bibl type="ancient">MTeh (Buber) 114 (3)</bibl> (-); <bibl type="ancient">YalqM Ps 68,3</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">אנדיקיס</term>)</note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Emendation acc. to <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 8a</bibl>. Cf. <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="egdiqos.html">אגדיקוס</ref> GenR.</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Sperber (1984)</title>
                  <citedRange>32</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
